This file explains the connection details to the embedded derby db

connection properties:

driver = "org.apache.derby.jdbc.EmbeddedDriver"
protocol = "jdbc:derby:"
dbName = "db"

procedure:

1. start Derby DB's interactive SQL scripting tool - ij
	java -cp .:./lib/derby.jar:./lib/derbytools.jar org.apache.derby.tools.ij

2. At the prompt, type in:
	connect 'jdbc:derby:db';

3. exit; to disconnect

4. show tables; to show all tables in the database
   The tables of interest to us are index and defaultselection


See http://db.apache.org/derby/papers/DerbyTut/ij_intro.html for more details.

